# Ultra-Detailed System Design Report: Smart Library Seat Detection

## 1. Executive Vision
The **Smart Library Seat Detection System** is an AI-driven ecosystem designed to transform library spatial management. By combining edge-computing computer vision with a centralized state-management architecture, it provides real-time, actionable insights into library utilization while maintaining student privacy and system scalability.

---

## 2. User Journey & Experience Flow
Understanding the interaction between the physical library space and the digital representation is critical.

```mermaid
journey
    title Student Experience Journey
    section Physical Action
      Student enters library: 5: Me
      Student looks for seat: 3: Me
      Student finds seat with bag: 4: Me
      Student sits down: 5: Me
    section Digital Interaction
      YOLO detects bag: 5: AI
      Seat marked RESERVED: 5: Dashboard
      YOLO detects person: 5: AI
      Seat marked OCCUPIED: 5: Dashboard
      Student leaves but keeps bag: 4: Me
      Seat stays RESERVED: 5: Dashboard
```

---

## 3. Technology Component Stack
The architecture is divided into specialized layers, each utilizing industry-standard technologies.

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Hardware & Capture"
        IPC[IP Camera / WebCam]
        RTSP[RTSP / HTTP Stream]
    end

    subgraph "Edge Intelligence (Python 3.10+)"
        YOLO_M[YOLOv8 Nano Model]
        CV2[OpenCV Image Processing]
        NP[NumPy Vector Math]
        POLYGON[Spatial Geometry Logic]
    end

    subgraph "Infrastructure & API (Flask)"
        F_SRV[Flask Web Server]
        CORS[Flask-CORS]
        JSON_INT[RESTful JSON Interface]
    end

    subgraph "Frontend Engine (React)"
        R_DOM[React Virtual DOM]
        CSS_MOD[Modular CSS/Glassmorphism]
        POLL[Axios/Fetch Polling]
    end

    IPC --> RTSP
    RTSP --> CV2
    CV2 --> YOLO_M
    YOLO_M --> POLYGON
    POLYGON --> JSON_INT
    JSON_INT --> F_SRV
    F_SRV --> R_DOM
```

